{"_id":"ir2Hasp17lDRl4nl","name":"Warp Weapon","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Reaction.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature you are observing Strikes you with a melee weapon attack.</p>\n<p>The attacking weapon gains the shoddy trait until the beginning of the attacker's next turn. If the -2 penalty from the shoddy trait would cause the attack to miss, it causes no damage. Natural weapons are unaffected by this ability.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["oracle"],"rarity":{"value":"common"},"custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.692,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2021-11-20T03:07:12.929-05:00","version":{"schema":0.652,"foundry":"0.8.9","system":"2.19.0.9009"}}},"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actionCategory":{"value":"defensive"},"actions":{"value":null},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"vkXZ1CDW49ufIquY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-actions.ir2Hasp17lDRl4nl"}}}
{"_id":"xv5kkmb344ZIxXUI","name":"Dynamic Mediumship","type":"action","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Frequency</strong> Once a day</p>\n<p><strong>Duration</strong> 1 hour</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong> You are currently pursuing at least one lead.</p>\n<p><strong>Special</strong> If done under a starry night, you can choose two spirits.</p>\n<p>You are able to channel the totemic spirits of particular animals to improve your ability to Pursue a Lead. You spend 10 minutes in a deep trance, during which you are considered @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Unconscious]{Unconscious}. Upon waking, the spirit of an animal enters your mind and body, granting you abilities dependent on the spirit's form.</p>\n<hr />\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Spirit of the Dog</strong> You gain scent as an imprecise sense at a range of 30 feet. Spirit of the Fox You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Will saving throws against the subjects of any of your investigations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-effects.HVrTcECgjmHT5oey]{effect: Spirit of the Dog}</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Spirit of the Weasel</strong> You gain low-light vision. If you already have low-light vision, you instead gain darkvision.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-effects.z2UidJusIrYGbt89]{Effect: Spirit of the Weasel}</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Spirit of the Stingray</strong> You gain electrolocation. Electrolocation is an imprecise sense with a range of 30 feet, allowing you to detect living creatures within the same body of water as yourself.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-effects.f6NGHIEmwxiotoYG]{Effect: Spirit of the Stingray}</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Spirit of the Panther</strong> You improve the circumstance bonus from Pursuing a Lead by 2 when attempting a Survival check to follow the tracks of a subject of one of your investigations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-effects.FIcgVIDy2C69Cndg]{Effect: Spirit of the Panther}</p>\n<p>If the subject of any of your investigations is an item, any creature in possession of that item is considered a subject of your investigation for the purposes of these abilities.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["concentrate","exploration","investigator"],"rarity":{"value":"common"},"custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.692,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2021-11-20T03:07:12.930-05:00","version":{"schema":0.652,"foundry":"0.8.9","system":"2.19.0.9009"}}},"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":"interaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"vkXZ1CDW49ufIquY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-actions.xv5kkmb344ZIxXUI"}}}
